  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Double-balloon endoscopy (DBE) is a new device that allows diagnosis and treatment throughout
      the entire small intestine. Although the originally described method requires two operators,
      the investigators have recently developed a method to perform DBE by a single operator. The
      investigators here assessed the clinical usefulness of this one-person method in comparison
      to the conventional two-person DBE.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
